  <h3 id="radio-happening-i">Radio Happening I</h3>
  <span class="item-meta">
    John Cage and Morton Feldman&nbsp;Â·&nbsp;1966
    
    <a href="https://www.ubu.com/sound/cage_feldman.html" target="_blank" class="item-link">â†—</a>
    
  </span>

</div>

<p>In 1966 and 1967, New York City station WBAI hosted a series of relaxed, informal, one-on-one conversations between composers John Cage and Morton Feldman. In the first of these â€œRadio Happenings,â€ Cage explains how his experience of the radio medium changed after using it as a compositional tool. He also (around 22:50 in the recording) describes an attitude toward sounds and their effects on listeners that we will consider as a type of programming. This cybernetic approach to experimental composition was expanded by other artists including Pauline Oliveros, and it will form one precdent for our artistic of deprogramming.</p>

